{"lemma":"طَعامٌ","slug":"طَعامٌ","root":"ط.ع.م","root_slug":"ط-ع-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ع-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"طَعام","root":"طعم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":24},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26738"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D8%B9%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"food","tags":["countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"قَالَ بَل لَّبِثْتَ مِائَةَ عَامٍ فَٱنْظُرْ إِلَى طَعَامِكَ وَشَرَابِكَ لَمْ يَتَسَنَّهْ","english":"He said, “Rather, you have remained one hundred years. Look at your food and your drink; it has not changed with time.”"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"food; prepared meal","tags":["countable","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"feeding","tags":["noun-from-verb"],"examples":[{"text":"وَلَا تَحَاضُّونَ عَلَى طَعَامِ ٱلْمِسْكِينِ","english":"And ye urge not on feeding the poor."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"wheat","tags":["al-Andalus","countable","uncountable"],"examples":[{"text":"وقيل إن نضح بقدر جرة من ماء الزيتون قدر مائة جرة من الطعام لم يفسد ولم تصبه آفة وإن نضح عليه ماء الأفسنتين بقي ولم يفسد.","english":"It is said that when a jar of wheat is dampened with a jar of amurca it does not suffer decay nor damage, and if it is dampened with absinthe water, it stays and does not rot."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"grain, cereal","tags":["countable","uncountable"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Cognate with Hebrew טַעַם (ṭāʿām)."},"ipa":["/tˤa.ʕaːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26738","headword_ar":"طَعَامٌ","root":"TEm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[as an inf. n.: see 1. ―         -b2-  As a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Food,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Nh, Mgh, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of any kind;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, TA;) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araAbN","text_ar":"شَرَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies beverage [of any kind]: (Mgh, Msb:) and especially"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Nh, Mgh, Msb, K,) to which it is applied by the people of El-Hijáz; (Msb, TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"barley;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, TA;) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corn"},{"kind":"text","text":"in general; thus applied to"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"millet"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the present day in some parts of Arabia, as, for instance, in El-Yemen; (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miyrapN","text_ar":"مِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":";)] and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, Mgh, TA,) when said not to mean wheat; (Mgh, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"&c.:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Nh, TA:) and in the Expos. of the “ Shifè, ” it is said to be applied to (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other than food"},{"kind":"text","text":"tropically: (TA:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuEomN","text_ar":"طُعْمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maToEamN","text_ar":"مَطْعَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Ham p. 166, and K; *) of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaAEimu","text_ar":"مَطَاعِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Ham ubi suprà:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yaHotakiru AlmaTaAEima","text_ar":"هُوَ يَحْتَكِرُ المَطَاعِمَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He collects and withholds"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wheat"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"waiting for a time of scarcity and dearness"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, TA:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAmN","text_ar":"طَعَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToEimapN","text_ar":"اَطْعِمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, K,) and pl. pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToEimaAtN","text_ar":"اَطْعِمَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) [It often means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A meal,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repast."},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaEaAmu AlbaHori","text_ar":"طَعَامُ البَحْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That from which the water"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the sea,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the great river,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has receded, leaving it, so that it is taken without fishing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is irrigated by the water of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bHr","text_ar":"بحر"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"great river"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and consequently vegetates:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so says Zj. (TA. [See the Kur v. 97.])"}],"source_refs":["S","Nh","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}